==English==
===Etymology=== 
From the Latin ''[[exstirpare]]'' "uproot"; ''[[ex-]]'' "out of" + ''[[stirp-]]'' "roots"

===Verb===
{{en-verb|extirpat|ing}}
# to pull up by the roots; [[uproot]]
# to [[destroy]] completely; to [[annihilate]]
# to [[surgically]] remove

====Synonyms====
*[[extricate]] (1)
*[[destroy]] (2)
*[[excise]] (3)

{{rfc}}
===Noun===
'''extirpation'''
# the act of extirpating

'''extirpator'''
# one who extirpates

=== Adjective ===
'''extirpative'''
# in the manner of extirpation

